  "question": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?",
  "prompt": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "160",
  "generated_text": "To find the total time Carla spends downloading the file, we need to break the process into two distinct phases: the initial download and the restart/re-download phase.\n\n**Phase 1: Initial Download**\n*   **Total file size:** $200 \\text{ GB}$\n*   **Download speed:** $2 \\text{ GB/minute}$\n*   **Time taken:**\n    $$ \\text{Time}_1 = \\frac{\\text{Total Size}}{\\text{Speed}} = \\frac{200}{2} = 100 \\text{ minutes} $$\n*   **Progress at the end of this phase:** $100 \\text{ minutes}$ is $100\\%$ of the $100 \\text{ minutes}$ required to download the entire file.\n*   **Check the restart condition:** The problem states \"40% of the way through the download\". Since $100\\% > 40\\%$, this condition is met.\n\n**Phase 2: Restart and Re-download**\n*   **Restart time:** $20 \\text{ minutes}$ (the problem states \"takes 20 minutes\" for the restart).\n*   **New download speed:** Since it is \"from the beginning\", the speed remains $2 \\text{ GB/minute}$.\n*   **Remaining size:** The file is $200 \\text{ GB}$, but $40\\%$ has already been downloaded in Phase 1.\n    $$ \\text{Remaining Size} = \\text{Total Size} - (\\text{Total Size} \\times 40\\%) $$\n    $$ \\text{Remaining Size} = 200 - (200 \\times 0.40) = 200 - 80 = 120 \\text{ GB} $$\n*   **Time taken for Phase 2:**\n    $$ \\text{Time}_2 = \\frac{\\text{Remaining Size}}{\\text{Speed}} = \\frac{120}{2} = 60 \\text{ minutes} $$\n*   **Total time for Phase 2:** This includes the restart time.\n    $$ \\text{Total}_2 = \\text{Restart Time} + \\text{Time}_2 = 20 + 60 = 80 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Total Time Calculation**\nThe total time to download the file is the sum of the time for the first phase and the total time for the second phase.\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = \\text{Time}_1 + \\text{Total}_2 $$\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = 100 + 80 = 180 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n\\boxed{180}\n",
